ABOUT MOHAMMED BIN ZAYED (MBZ) CITY

Commonly known as MBZ City, Mohammed Bin Zayed City is a quiet residential suburb in the mainland of Abu Dhabi. The area is almost completely developed with a few villas under construction here and there. It lies between the planned mega project of Zayed City (Khalifa City C) and Mussaffah allowing direct access to main highways. BANIYAS

Baniyas is an urban community in Abu Dhabi located along the Abu Dhabi-Al Ain highway towards the south of Abu Dhabi. The neighbourhood is categorised into two sub-communities – Baniyas West and Baniyas East. It is surrounded by popular communities such as Al Mafraq, Shakhbout City, Al Wathba, Al Shawamekh, Al Shamkha and Mohammed Bin Zayed City.

The area is developed by Baniyas Investment & Development Company (BIDC). The focus of BIDC was to help the area develop into a modern community while maintaining the emirate’s rich cultural heritage. The capital city witnessed tremendous development in recent times including many high-rise buildings with modern apartments to add to the residential side. Baniyas is known for housing the Baniyas Sports and Culture Club, a sports complex that also hosts the Baniyas football team.
